{
  "doc_id": "15151",
  "text": "Fucoidan was reported to induce a reduction in some types of human cancer cell lines in a dose-dependent manner [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , and clinical trials of fucoidan ingested in human subjects had given promising results [CITATION_3] . However, more research is required in order to promote the use of fucoidan for potential chemotherapeutic treatments. Sulfate content and molecular weight (Mw) of fucoidan polymers have been reported to have a direct relationship to fucoidans' cytotoxicity and because fucoidan is a polymer mixture, fucoidans extracted from different seaweed or different locations have different bioactivity [CITATION_4] . However, cytotoxicity of lower and higher Mw fucoidans have not been investigated [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] .",
